{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"34224a45-ec67-4865-82dc-dfe690633e91","content":"You already have the HotReload package referenced — you just need to run `dotnet test` with the `--hotreload` flag:\n\n```\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a **watch mode** that:\n1. Runs your tests immediately\n2. Watches for source file changes\n3. Automatically re-runs tests when you save edits (using hot reload, so it's fast — no full rebuild)\n\n**Your current issue:** `IsValidEmail` only checks for non-empty strings — it doesn't check for `@`. So `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` will fail. With hot reload running, you can fix `IsValidEmail` and see results instantly on save.\n\nWant me to fix the failing test logic and demonstrate?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a0f63d42-fc2d-4139-a523-d36df77ff02d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to use HotReload to iterate on fixing the tests. Let me explain the workflow.\n\nThe project already has `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` referenced. The key is to use `dotnet test --hotreload` which watches for file changes and re-runs tests automatically.\n\nLet me first show the failing tests and then explain the hot reload workflow.","outputTokens":281,"requestId":"7C20:203FDB:28AA16A:2D12145:69F949F3"},"id":"6896fa2c-862a-4a5c-9bce-e0f0c34d0df9","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:38:04.642Z","parentId":"36b63bd6-9b16-4049-887a-c45db0eaf01e"}
